Introduction
============

  In this file you will find how to use Liner2. To find the installation 
  guideline please see INSTALL. To find the license terms please see LICENSE.

  This is only brief introduction to Liner2. To see the complete description
  of Liner2 options please visit: http://nlp.pwr.wroc.pl/redmine/projects/inforex-liner/wiki

Models
======

  The Liner2 package contains a simple model called model-5nam-v1 for recognition
  of 5 categories of proper names (first names, last names, names of countries,
  cities and roads).

  Additional models can be found at http://nlp.pwr.wroc.pl/en/tools-and-resources/liner2

   * model-56nam-v1.7z --- 56 categories of proper names (complete list of names
     can be found here http://nlp.pwr.wroc.pl/en/tools-and-resources/nelexicon).
     Download: wget http://nlp.pwr.wroc.pl/download/liner2/model-56nam-v1.7z

  To use another model then default you can modify the local.ini file or provide
  the -ini {path} parameter in the command line. The -ini parameter from command
  line override the -ini parameter from the local.ini file.
  
Usage
=====
    
  * Pipe mode (to process a single document), read and write in ccl format:

      ./liner2.sh pipe -ini model-5nam-v1/model.ini -i ccl -f test/sentence.xml -o ccl

    or with global command and default configuration:
  
      liner2 -i ccl -f test/sentence.xml -o ccl

  * Interactive mode with preprocessed data:

      ./liner2.sh batch -ini model-56nam-v1/model.ini -o tuples
  
    == Input ==
    Pani Pani subst:sg:nom:f  Jadwiga Jadwiga subst:sg:nom:f  Nowak Nowak subst:sg:nom:m1  z z prep:gen:nwok  Krakowa Kraków subst:sg:gen:m3
  
    == Output ==
    (4,10,PERSON_FIRST_NAM,"Jadwiga")
    (11,15,PERSON_LAST_NAM,"Nowak")
  

  * Interactive mode for raw text (requires maca):

      ./liner2.sh batch -ini model-56nam-v1/model.ini -i plain -o tuples -maca -

    == Input ==
    Pani Jadwiga Nowak z Krakowa

    == Output ==
    (4,10,PERSON_FIRST_NAM,"Jadwiga")
    (11,15,PERSON_LAST_NAM,"Nowak")
